[log] bash[68] stdout #### 1. _AttributeHolder
[log] bash[68] stdout **Function**: Abstract base class that provides __repr__. Provides a basic class for attribute access, used to store and manage object attribute information.
[log] bash[68] stdout ```python
[log] bash[68] stdout class _AttributeHolder(object):
[log] bash[68] stdout     def __repr__(self) """Return string representation of the object."""
[log] bash[68] stdout     def _get_kwargs(self) """Get keyword arguments for the object."""
[log] bash[68] stdout     def _get_args(self) """Get positional arguments for the object."""
[log] bash[68] stdout ```
[log] bash[68] stdout **Parameter Description**: No parameters, serves as base class for attribute containers.
[log] bash[68] stdout **Method Return Values**:
[log] bash[68] stdout - `__repr__()`: Returns string representation
[log] bash[68] stdout - `_get_kwargs()`: Returns list of keyword argument tuples
[log] bash[68] stdout - `_get_args()`: Returns list of positional arguments
