[log] bash[68] stdout `_MutuallyExclusiveGroup` is used to create a group of mutually exclusive command-line arguments. This means that at most one argument from this group can appear in the command line. For example, you can use it to define a set of options such as `--verbose` and `--quiet`, where the user can only specify one of them.
[log] bash[68] stdout **Class Signature**:
[log] bash[68] stdout ```python
